         <h2>Online Help for EXCHANGE RATE Object</h2>
<br></br><br></br>
This object is to manage Standard Selling Exchange Rate and Standard Buying Exchange Rate.<br></br>
Non-Standard Exchange Rate designated to specific customers and partners is prior than Standard Exchange Rate.<br></br>
<br></br>
In case the companies selected in Invoice To/Payment To in H B/L Selling/Buying are defined at Non-Standard Exchange Rate,<br></br>
Non-Standard Exchange Rate will be synchronized to H B/L Shipment, H B/L Selling/Buying, M B/L Buying.<br></br>
<br></br>
In case the companies selected in Invoice To/Payment To in H B/L Selling/Buying are not defined at Non-Standard Exchange Rate,<br></br>
Standard Rate will be synchronized to H B/L Shipment, H B/L Selling/Buying, M B/L Buying.<br></br>
<br></br>
Selling Standard Rate which is syncrhonized to H B/L Shipment, H B/L Selling/Buying, M B/L Buying.<br></br>
-SELLING EX-RATE TO FORWARDING CUSTOMER<br></br>
-SELLING EX-RATE TO CC(Custom Clearance) CUSTOMER<br></br>
-SELLING EX-RATE TO PARTNER-STANDARD <br></br>
<br></br>
Buying Standard Rate which is sychronized to H B/L Shipment, H B/L Selling/Buying, M B/L Buying.<br></br>
-BUYING EX-RATE FROM PARTNER-STANDARD<br></br>
  
